{"_id":"baNnflkuTcpKCp5Q","name":"Crit Table M: Monsters","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.SA5nnmEvoSyAfOLE"}},"content":"<p>pg. 392</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-crits-and-fumbles.TCbqZHYTwnE5HB0s]{Crit Table M: Monsters}</p>\n<table style=\"height: 765px; width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1 or less</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Strike to chest, breaking ribs. This attack inflicts +[[/roll 1d6]] damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Stunning blow! The PC falls to the bottom of the initiative count for the remainder of the battle.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Legs knocked out from beneath the character, knocking him prone.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">PC disarmed. Weapon lands [[/roll 1d12+5]]&rsquo; away.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Blow to shield arm! If no shield, this attack inflicts +[[/roll 1d6]] damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Weapon lodged in PC&rsquo;s chest! This attack inflicts +{/roll [[/roll 2d6]] damage and an additional [[/roll 1d6]] damage next round.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">7</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Blow to jaw! The PC loses [[/roll 1d8]] hp and the same number of teeth.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">8</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Blow shatters PC&rsquo;s forearm. This attack inflicts +[[/roll 1d6]] damage, and the arm is useless until healed.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">9</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Strike to helm! If no helmet, this attack inflicts +[[/roll 1d8]] damage and forces a Fort save (DC 10 + HD). On a failed save, the PC falls unconscious.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">10</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Stunning blow! The world spins as the fell monster makes a second attack! 11 Strike to throat! The PC can&rsquo;t speak until healed and spends the next round struggling to breathe.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">12</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Blow smashes PC&rsquo;s kneecap. The character&rsquo;s movement is cut by half and this attack inflicts +[[/roll 1d10]] damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">13</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Crushing blow! This attack inflicts +[[/roll 1d12]] damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">14</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">PC&rsquo;s weapon sundered in the violent assault.*</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">15</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Strike to torso crushes internal organs. This attack inflicts +[[/roll 1d12]] damage, and force the PC to make Fort save (DC 15 + HD) to remain conscious through the pain.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">16</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Devastating strike! This attack inflicts +[[/roll 1d16]] damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">17</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">PC&rsquo;s Achilles tendon is torn, snapping back into his thigh. The character&rsquo;s movement drops to 5&rsquo; and the screaming can be heard for leagues.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">18</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Monster seizes PC by the neck. This attack inflicts +[[/roll 1d12]] damage and the monster makes a second attack at +4 to hit.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">19</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Blow to cranium! This attack inflicts +[[/roll 1d16]] damage and the PC must make a Fort save (DC 15 + HD) or fall unconscious.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">20</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Terrifying blow pierces several important organs. The PC spends the next [[/roll 1d4]] days dying a slow, painful death. Powerful magic (healing by a cleric of level 3 or higher) can arrest the dying.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">21</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Strike crushes skull, destroying the optic nerve and resulting in instant, permanent blindness.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">22</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">PC&rsquo;s leg is shorn from his body. The character cannot move. This attack inflicts +[[/roll 2d12]] damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">23</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Both the PC&rsquo;s arms are torn from his body. This attack inflicts +[[/roll 3d12]] damage. Exceptionally cruel monsters may proceed to use PC&rsquo;s arms as weapons.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">24</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">PC is disemboweled. Bloody guts spill to the ground. The PC spends the next 8 rounds dying as he futilely tries to feed the spooling intestines back into his body.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">25</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Attack craters PC&rsquo;s skull. This attack inflicts [[/roll 1d8]] Intelligence and Personality damage and puts the PC into an instant coma.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">26</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Strike crushes throat. The PC drowns in his own blood for 6 rounds.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">27</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Attack snaps the PC&rsquo;s spinal column like a twig. The attack causes permanent paralysis, and the PC watches the remainder of the battle from the floor.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">28</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Throat torn asunder. The panicked PC gargles wetly as blood gouts down his chest. He dies in 4 rounds.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%;\">29</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%;\">Terrible blow to the chest explodes the PC&rsquo;s heart. Immediate and instantaneous death.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9208%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">30</td>\n<td style=\"width: 85.7919%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Attack rends PC&rsquo;s head from his torso. Blood gouts from the collapsing body, and the monster moves on to the next foe, making attacks until it misses.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">* Magical weapons never break due to critical fumbles. The target is disarmed instead, the weapon landing</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> [[/roll 1d10+5]] </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">feet away.</span></em></p>"}
{"_id":"bwoiXE9CPr8r1s48","name":"Experience Points","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.Jb0VwISl0kz9NzrV"}},"content":"<p>pg. 359</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>While brave adventurers explore strange dungeons, their compatriots toil in the fields, threshing wheat under a burning sun. When the adventurers emerge back into the sunlight who will be the higher level, them or their farmer friends? As just noted, only 1 in 100 men reach level 2&mdash;and only 1 in 10,000 reaches level 5. Whether farmer or fulgurator, level advancement is a slow, measured progress. Survival is its own reward; preeminence, a bonus.<br /><br />In general, practicing one&rsquo;s profession earns experience points (XP), and accumulation of XP produces advancement in level. Adventurers practice their profession by challenging themselves in dangerous situations&mdash;usually, but not always, combat.<br /><br /><strong>Scaling XP Awards:</strong> As introduced in the characters chapter, XP are a measure of level advancement. Your job as judge is to award XP to the players as they complete encounters. XP are always rewarded by encounter not creature or challenge. In general, most level-appropriate encounters should be worth 2 XP, with the scale going from 0 to 4 as follows:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1549%; height: 102px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 5.87392%; height: 17px;\"><strong>XP</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 93.4157%; height: 17px;\"><strong>Description</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 5.87392%; height: 17px;\">0</td>\n<td style=\"width: 93.4157%; height: 17px;\">Very easy encounter with little to no damage or resource loss for the&nbsp; adventurers. This is the kind of encounter that no longer challenges a group and clearly does not advance their skill level.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 5.87392%; height: 17px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 93.4157%; height: 17px;\">An encounter with damage and resource expenditure but relatively easy&nbsp; nonetheless. The typical &ldquo;easy encounter&rdquo; falls into this bracket.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 5.87392%; height: 17px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 93.4157%; height: 17px;\">A typical encounter. The characters incurred damage and were required to utilize resources to survive the encounter. No fatalities or significant losses.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 5.87392%; height: 17px;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 93.4157%; height: 17px;\">A difficult encounter, even with good tactics. Significant damage and potentially permanent consequences, possibly even a fatality.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 5.87392%; height: 17px;\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 93.4157%; height: 17px;\">An extremely difficult encounter, one that the party barely survives. Multiple character fatalities, significant character damage, and potentially a retreat of some kind required.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>XP for Non-Combat Activities:</strong> XP is always rewarded for combat. Non-combat encounters may also be worth experience points. Disarming or setting off traps provides guidance to characters of what to do (or not to do) in the future. Puzzles likewise build experience in navigating a dungeon. In broader terms, these criteria for earning XP can be interpreted as &ldquo;bypassing hazards&rdquo;; advancing past dangerous situations warrants the earning of XP. Thieves should receive XP for bypassing traps (typically 1-2 points, depending on the nature of the trap), and puzzles should likewise be worth XP to all who participated in solving them.<br /><br />The judge may also choose to award XP for mundane, classrelated activities. Just as there are level 2 wizards, there are also level 2 farmers and other non-character professions. These peasants advance through non-combat activities, and characters can, too. The rate of advancement for such activities is very slow&mdash;typically 1 XP for every period of activity. For a farmer, a period of activity might be one planting season; for a blacksmith, it could be a full year of&nbsp; work.<br /><br />Characters can likewise be rewarded for non-combat activities as appropriate to their class, typically at the rate of 1-2 XP for every significant non-combat event. Here are some examples of appropriate non-combat events:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Warrior</strong>: hiring a trainer to train in weapons, martial arts, archery, jousting, and other military activities; constructing a citadel or sailing vessel; hiring or recruiting men-at-arms to build a militia; equipping an expedition; paying tribute to a higher-ranking lord; and so on.</li>\n<li><strong>Cleric:</strong> tithing to a temple on an ongoing basis; constructing a shrine, altar, or idol; donating to the needy; equipping a pilgrimage; translating or restoring sacred scrolls; recruiting followers; and so on.</li>\n<li><strong>Wizard:</strong> forging magic items; researching or creating new magical spells; building a wizard&rsquo;s tower; building a golem or homunculus; acquiring rare or valuable spell components; and so on.</li>\n<li><strong>Thief:</strong> paying for information; spending on drinks, food, and entertainment to establish contacts; acquiring blackmail material; constructing traps; building a secret vault; and so on.</li>\n<li><strong>Elf:</strong> any activities associated with a warrior or wizard.</li>\n<li><strong>Dwarf:</strong> any activities associated with a warrior.</li>\n<li><strong>Halfling:</strong> any activities associated with a warrior or a thief.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br /><strong>Advancing in Level:</strong> When a character accrues enough XP to advance in level (per the XP table on page 26), he automatically acquires the benefits of that new level. No formalized training or other activity is necessary&mdash;though, as mentioned above, spending gold on training may accelerate the process</p>"}
{"_id":"cUCBkV5j1uyqFEPD","name":"Table 9-7: Unusual Traits","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.Xpvxsvvc2mqFv7FX"}},"content":"<p>g. 383</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Demons have personality quirks, too. There is a 5% chance that any given monster has an unusual trait. Here are 12 ideas:</span></p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-tables.zVO6euTPJ5gUW48F]{Table 9-7: Unusual Traits}</p>\n<table style=\"height: 272px; width: 70.1755%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"530\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 34px;\">[[/roll 1d12]]</td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 34px;\"><strong>Trait</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Sneezes constantly</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">2</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Smells like butter</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">3</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Strange warts</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">4</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Incredibly ugly &ndash; the ugliest example of that creature the heroes have ever seen</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">5</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Bad halitosis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">6</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Alopecia (And yes, before you ask, there is such a thing as a self-conscious pit fiend with a combover&hellip;)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">7</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">A bad flu &ndash; coughing, sneezing, runny nose</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">8</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Flatulent</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">9</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Loquacious</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">10</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Toothless</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">11</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Whistles incessantly</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10.178%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">12</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.5379%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Two left feet</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
{"_id":"d1mIzX7GNK5kHtTm","name":"Table 9-6: Traits or Properties of Un-dead","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.JuV3cSnar2T2xWd1"}},"content":"<p>pg. 381</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-tables.YMnCVib1mz24LYCp]{Table 9-6: Traits or Properties of Un-dead}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%; height: 367px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"530\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\">[[/roll 1d20]]</td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\"><strong>Trait or Property</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Energy-draining touch (ability score damage; Will save resists)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">2</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Level-draining touch (lose XP; Will save resists)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">3</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Searing gaze ([[/roll 1d6]] damage with a look)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">4</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Touch of cold ([[/roll 1d4]] damage; immune to fire spells)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">5</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Chill aura (all within 100&rsquo; take [[/roll 1d4]] damage; immune to fire spells)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">6</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Blood drain (causes [[/roll 1d4]] damage + 1 Stamina point each round)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">7</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Flight</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">8</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Transformation (rat, cat, bat, wolf, worm; or mist, dust, spirit; etc.)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">9</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Extraordinary strength (Str 22+)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">10</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Swift (2 actions per round)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">11</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Slow (1 action every 2 rounds)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">12</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Immune to non-magical weapons</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">13</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Immune to non-silvered weapons</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">14</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Resistant to spells (50% chance of any spell not affecting it)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">15</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Cannot be killed without special ritual (stake through heart, exorcism, destruction of phylactery, form burned in fire, etc.)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">16</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Paralysis with touch (Will save to resist)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">17</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Translucent/transparent/invisible</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">18</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Issues a curse with every strike (see Appendix C)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">19</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Casts spells as wizard of level [[/roll 1d4+1]]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 10px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.2534%; height: 10px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">20</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 86.4593%; height: 10px;\" align=\"left\">Continues to worship a dark god in undeath; casts spells as cleric of level [[/roll 1d4+1]]; can turn living as a cleric turns unholy</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
{"_id":"dUm6pTYpzZdPu58j","name":"Table 8-9: Sword Powers, Type III: Magical","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.plZpzcxcPqDpwPW3"}},"content":"<p>pg. 371</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-tables.t2NrFoZNcKhtrH1b]{Table 8-9: Sword Powers, Type III: Magical}</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"100\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"511\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"23\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td align=\"justify\"><strong>Power</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"29\">01-07</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Spell healer. Wielder heals spellburn at 3x the normal rate: with no rest, heals 3 points of ability score loss each night, and with rest, heals 6 points each night.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"42\">08-14</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Spellburn reservoir. Each day, the wielder can burn up to 3 points of the sword&rsquo;s Intelligence on spellburn to affect his spellcasting as if he were spellburning his own abilities. The sword&rsquo;s lost ability scores heal in full each night.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">15-20</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Spell magnifier. The wielder casts all spells at +1 caster level.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"42\">21-25</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Shift planes. The wielder can shift to an adjacent plane 1/day, arriving in the position corresponding to his current position. There is a 10% chance that the sword also allows him to take along up to [[/roll 1d4+1]] allies with each plane shift.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"42\">26-30</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Demon-binding. With any successful strike against a demon or other extraplanar creature, the target must make a DC 20 Will save or be bound to its current exact location for [[/roll 1d4]] turns. It cannot take any steps or teleport out unless this effect is magically dispelled.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"28\">31-39</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Summon creature. The sword is magically keyed to a specific creature type (e.g., wolf, lion, pegasus, etc.). The wielder can summon such a creature [[/roll 1d3]] times per day.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"56\">40-51</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Resistance. The sword grants its wielder resistance to certain forms of attack. The wielder ignores the first 3 points of damage from that form of attack each round, and gains a +1 bonus to saving throws against that form of damage. The form of attack is (roll [[/roll 1d6]]) (1) fire, (2) cold, (3) acid, (4) lightning, (5) poison, (6) drowning.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"42\">52-58</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Immune to non-magical attacks. The sword makes its wielder resistant to non-magical attacks. The wielder resists the first 5 points of damage each round by attacks of a non-magical nature. Creatures of 5+ HD are considered &ldquo;magical&rdquo; for purposes of this effect.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"56\">59-65</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Resistance to critical hits. The sword makes the wielder hard to inflict critical damage upon. The wielder receives an automatic Fort save whenever a critical occurs against him. The DC is equal to the natural die roll used to score the crit (usually 20 but not always). If he makes this save, the critical does not take effect.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">66-75</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Flight. The wielder can fly at a speed of 30&rsquo;.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"28\">76-84</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Turn invisible. Up to [[/roll 1d3]] times per day, the wielder can turn invisible for a duration of [[/roll 1d4]] turns. The invisibility vanishes immediately if the wielder attacks.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">85-90</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Magic resistance. All spells directed specifically at the wielder suffer a -2 spell check penalty.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">91-94</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Supreme willpower. The wielder receives a +2 bonus to Will saves.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"28\">95-97</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Un-dead touch. The weapon scores critical hits as an un-dead creature, rolling [[/roll 1d30]] on crit table U whenever a crit is scored.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"28\">98-00</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Regeneration. As long as he wields this weapon in his hand, the wielder regenerates 1 point of damage each round.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
{"_id":"dshmsEpriCQbT5bl","name":"Patron Taint: Azi Dahaka","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.E2AWS6zGFYB0w9rc"}},"content":"<p>pg. 330</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.LcIOsjt1ph7scO5n]{Patron Taint: Azi Dahaka}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1-1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">Casting any spell produces a light coat of fine dust, which settles over everything within 20&rsquo; of the caster</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">The caster&rsquo;s spells draw destructive storms of unnatural wrath. There is a 10% chance after casting any spell that thunder booms somewhere in the distance. If the Result is rolled a second time, any time the caster casts a spell, there is a 35% chance it is following by the immediate crash of localized thunder in [[/roll 1d5]] seconds. If the result is rolled a third time, there is a 50% chance that any spell causes a flash of lightning and the immediate crack of thunder. Those within 20&rsquo; of the caster must succeed on a DC 10 Fort save of be deafened for [[/roll 1d4]] rounds.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3-3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">The caster&rsquo;s presence brings ruin and decay to all things. Wooden and paper objects decay at his touch, crumbling into ash after a single week. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster&rsquo;s touch reduces cloth and leather to rags and then ash, after only ten days. If the result is rolled a third time, the caster&rsquo;s touch causes metal to rust and decay, crumbling into sand in a month&rsquo;s time. Magical objects resist the caster&rsquo;s casual touch, but still show wear where previously there was none, becoming pitted, mottled and worn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4-4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">Patches of the caster&rsquo;s torso skin peel away to reveal iridescent scales. If the Result is rolled a second time, the skin on the caster&rsquo;s arms and legs is transformed into scales. If the result is rolled a third time, the caster&rsquo;s skin molts, revealing a body covered by scales.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">5-5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">The caster&rsquo;s wounds weep clear ooze&mdash; an offering to Azi Dahaka that leaves the caster parched and dry. Anytime the caster takes a wound, he loses 1 additional hp due to the seeping ooze. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster develops weeping sores on his body</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">6-6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">The caster takes on the aspect of Azi Dahaka, as a second pair of eyes buds somewhere on his shoulders or back. A ruin mutation, the eyes are blind, but blink disconcertingly every few moments. If the Result is rolled a second time, two more sets of eyes bud somewhere on the caster&rsquo;s shoulders and back. If the result is rolled a third time, the budding faces fully emerge from the caster&rsquo;s body. The mouths moan strange dirges to Azi Dahaka in forgotten tongues, the nostrils flare wildly, and the blind eyes dart about unpredictably, as if tracking unseen beings.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br /><br /></p>"}
{"_id":"eS7ASAYPDvsezFw9","name":"Spellburn: Azi Dahaka","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.8DSCS7W8zrRDw7oU"}},"content":"<p>pg. 332</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spellburn-actions.XWfHFMLTnc10LZVW]{Azi Dahaka Spellburn Actions}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 8.53739%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.7443%;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 8.53739%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1-1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.7443%;\" align=\"left\">The power of the spellburn opens the caster to the maddening horrors of the universe and leaves him weak (expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss) and disoriented. The caster must succeed on a DC 15 Will save or be unable to cast spells for [[/roll 1d3]] rounds. If the caster succeeds on the save, the caster gains a +1 bonus to all future attempts at the spell.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 8.53739%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.7443%;\" align=\"left\">Admiring the caster&rsquo;s ambition, Sezrekan grants the caster the opportunity to burn an ally&rsquo;s attributes (Stamina, Strength or Agility) in place of his own. The target must be willing. For every point burned to augment the spell, the target loses [[/roll 1d3]] points of the same attribute. If any of the target&rsquo;s attributes fall to 0 or less, the target dies.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 8.53739%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3-3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.7443%;\" align=\"left\">Sezrekan mocks the caster&rsquo;s feeble grasps at power. The caster receives but 1 point for every 2 points of attribute burned.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 8.53739%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4-4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.7443%;\" align=\"left\">Horrific madness seizes the caster&rsquo;s mind, and the awful meaninglessness of the universe is driven deep into his mortal soul. The caster is granted a single DC 15 Will save</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br /><br /></p>"}
{"_id":"eeLCj76wsZGQexuh","name":"Spellburn: Bobugbubilz","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.vmkilB6hycjqqPK1"}},"content":"<p>pg. 324</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spellburn-actions.RE9mEcN8XaWBHGkR]{Bobugbubilz Spellburn Actions}</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.30161%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.98%;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.30161%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1-1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.98%;\" align=\"left\">Bobugbubilz needs the blood of a dry-dweller (a creature that lives only on land). The caster&rsquo;s blood will do (expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.30161%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.98%;\" align=\"left\">The demon lord of amphibians needs the feet of a man-creature. In this special situation, the character can spellburn up to 10 points of ability score loss, but need not take any physical action or damage. If he sacrifices the feet of a man-creature (any humanoid will do) to Bobugbubilz before the next sunrise, the character takes no spellburn. If he fails to find such a sacrifice, he takes the full 10 points, distributed across ability scores at the judge&rsquo;s discretion, at the next sunrise.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.30161%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3-3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.98%;\" align=\"left\">Bobugbubilz requires the sweet voice of the caster to make an invocation that his own amphibious servants cannot pronounce properly. Time slows to a crawl as the caster character is whisked away to a dizzying plane of close-quartered, moist, womb-like caverns, where he is forced to read a text written in the words of his native language but with a recondite meaning utterly beyond his comprehension. Upon completing the invocation, he appears back on his native plane. No time seems to have passed, and he finds himself weakened by whatever extent he sacrificed ability score points for spellburn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.30161%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4-4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 89.98%;\" align=\"left\">A slithering host of foul serpents wriggles forth from the ground at the caster&rsquo;s feet, where they promptly bite his ankles and begin sucking his blood. If the caster resists, the serpents flee and the spellburn fails. If he does not resist, the serpents suck blood until the spellburn is complete as normal, then they wriggle back into the earth. As they disappear below the ground, one turns its head back to offer thanks from Bobugbubilz&hellip;then it is gone.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"emZdegbZO0F7RpHI","name":"Table 7-3: What componenents are required for the spell to function?","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.Wl1kqcIftJGLO7T1"}},"content":"<p>pg. 316</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-tables.kXs0BB58F8gLFQka]{Table 7-3: What components are required for the spell to function?}</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"64\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"558\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"18\"><strong> [[/roll 1d10]]</strong></td>\n<td align=\"left\"><strong> Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"28\">1</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Dragon&rsquo;s scale</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"31\">2</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Medusa&rsquo;s eye</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"29\">3</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Harpy&rsquo;s feather</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Basilisk&rsquo;s gaze</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">5</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Virgin&rsquo;s pure heart</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"41\">6</td>\n<td align=\"left\">The blood of an un-dead</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"41\">7</td>\n<td align=\"left\">A hyena&rsquo;s bark</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"33\">8</td>\n<td align=\"left\">A mother&rsquo;s love for her child</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">9</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Utterance of a seventh son</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">10</td>\n<td align=\"left\">The most brilliant diamond</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
