entice</td>\n<td style=\"width: 24.2912%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Dagger</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.5546%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Black grimoire</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.9181%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">98-100</td>\n<td style=\"width: 28.9487%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Woodcutter</td>\n<td style=\"width: 24.2912%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Handaxe</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.5546%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Bundle of wood</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><em>&dagger; If a missile fire weapon (such as sling or dart), roll [[/roll 1d6]] to determine number of sling stones or darts.</em><br /><em>* Roll </em>[[/roll 1d8]]<em> to determine farmer type: (1) potato, (2) wheat, (3) turnip, (4) corn, (5) rice, (6) parsnip, (7) radish, (8) rutabaga.</em><br /><em>** Why did the chicken cross the hallway? To check for traps! In all seriousness, if the party includes more than one farmer or herder, randomly determine the second and subsequent farm animals for each duplicated profession with </em>[[/roll 1d6]]<em>: (1) sheep, (2) goat, (3) cow, (4) duck, (5) goose, (6) mule.</em><br /><em>*** Roll </em>[[/roll 1d6]] <em>to determine what&rsquo;s in the cart: (1) tomatoes, (2) nothing, (3) straw, (4) your dead, (5) dirt, (6) rocks.</em></p>"}
{"_id":"ow91jNPnNjWzhZeJ","name":"Spellburn: The Three Fates","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.p9gOSR9kesucOfW9"}},"content":"<p>pg. 350</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spellburn-actions.ApIaXAN5MsIKHoV9]{The Three Fates Spellburn Actions}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.4192%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 5.66673%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"74\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 93.8465%;\" align=\"left\">Apprehending the majesty of his role in the ordered universe exhausts the caster (expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss). The caster must succeed on a DC 15 Will save or lose all benefits of the spellburn. If the caster succeeds on the save, his hard-won wisdom grants him a +1 bonus to all future attempts at the spell. (Such a bonus can only be gained once per spell.)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 5.66673%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"57\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 93.8465%;\" align=\"left\">The caster draws upon the latent power of ley lines and telluric currents, utilizing the native forces to empower his spell. On a successful Int check (DC 15+spell level), the caster gains +3 to his spell check without expending any stats. (The caster is then free to spellburn stats to further augment the casting.)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 5.66673%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"62\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 93.8465%;\" align=\"left\">The caster submits himself to the will of the Fates, who drain the caster of stat points according to their own, unknowable plan. Roll [[/roll 1d4]] to determine the stat drained in the spellburn: 1 Strength, 2 Agility, 3 Stamina, 4 the caster suffers no drain but still receives the spellburn bonus.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 5.66673%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"60\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 93.8465%;\" align=\"left\">The caster cannot spellburn without resorting to a fell chaos rite. His oppressive guilt and the spell&rsquo;s grim requirements are expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss. Should the caster ever spellburn in the presence of other agents of the Fates, his life would surely be forfeit.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"ozxzqhAVK2QxIs9j","name":"Spellburn: Sezrekan","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.A9jX4xqnlE5qDbc7"}},"content":"<p>pg. 338</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spellburn-actions.YanqOfsEBkofHpn6]{Sezrekan Spellburn Actions}</p>\n<table style=\"height: 221px; width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"34\"></colgroup><colgroup width=\"2169\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.33249%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.3801%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.33249%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1-1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.3801%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\">The power of the spellburn opens the caster to the maddening horrors of the universe and leaves him weak (expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss) and disoriented. The caster must succeed on a DC 15 Will save or be unable to cast spells for [[/roll 1d3]] rounds. If the caster succeeds on the save, the caster gains a +1 bonus to all future attempts at the spell.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.33249%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.3801%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\">Admiring the caster&rsquo;s ambition, Sezrekan grants the caster the opportunity to burn an ally&rsquo;s attributes (Stamina, Strength or Agility) in place of his own. The target must be willing. For every point burned to augment the spell, the target loses [[/roll 1d3]] points of the same attribute. If any of the target&rsquo;s attributes fall to 0 or less, the target dies.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.33249%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3-3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.3801%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Sezrekan mocks the caster&rsquo;s feeble grasps at power. The caster receives but 1 point for every 2 points of attribute burned.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.33249%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4-4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.3801%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Horrific madness seizes the caster&rsquo;s mind, and the awful meaninglessness of the universe is driven deep into his mortal soul. The caster is granted a single DC 15 Will save</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
{"_id":"pEYRr4enrBKuIr6H","name":"Azi Dahaka","permission":{"default":0,"l6YjvvzdQ7bk09DR":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.3Kyyw1IFzRfQfWQo"}},"content":"<p>pg. 330</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The demon prince of storms and waste, Azi Dahaka is anything but subtle. He is the blasting sand storm, the deadly asp, and the desiccated corpse in scorching sun. He appears as an infernal hydra and expects his followers to bring ruin wherever they go. Eventually the world shall be a desert - over which he will rule. His ceremony must be conducted in a desert at high noon where the caster has imbibed no liquid for one day and one night before. He demands much of his followers, causing them to be dehydrated and experience heat-induced visions where he gives them minor quests related to spreading chaos.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Invoke Patron check results:</strong></p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-patron.mojUc7iLhA2PFjXX]{Invoke Azi Dahaka}@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-patron.5RHGsjr7N1UmCj1U]{Invoke Azi Dahaka}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%; height: 527px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"2978\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; height: 17px; text-align: left;\" align=\"right\" height=\"17\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (3 or less) @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.q9g7zkrhqhZIJapP]{Invoke Azi Dahaka Corruption}+&nbsp;<span class=\"fontstyle0\">@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.LcIOsjt1ph7scO5n]{Patron Taint: Azi Dahaka} (4-5) @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.q9g7zkrhqhZIJapP]{Invoke Azi Dahaka Corruption}; (6+) @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.LcIOsjt1ph7scO5n]{Patron Taint: Azi Dahaka}.</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; text-align: left; height: 17px;\">2-11</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 17px;\">Failure. Unlike other spells, invoke patron may not be lost for the day. Depending on the results of patron bond, the wizard may still be able to cast it.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">12-13</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Azi Dahaka sends a bolt of static lightning toward one of the caster&rsquo;s enemies, causing [[/roll 2d6]] damage (DC 15 Fort save for half). The caster can designate any target within 100&rsquo;.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">14-17</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\">A cyclone erupts around the caster&rsquo;s enemies. The caster and his allies are unaffected, but all other creatures within a 30&rsquo; radius of the caster suffer [[/roll 1d8]] points of abrasion damage per round. Additionally, each round, all enemies within the cyclone must make a Reflex save or be knocked prone by the storming winds. The cyclone continues for [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">18-19</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\">A sandstorm fills the air with blinding dust. However, the caster and his allies can still see normally. Enemies within a 60&rsquo; radius are blinded as long as the caster continues to concentrate, for up to 1 minute.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">20-23</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\">A diminutive asp slithers forth from the caster&rsquo;s sleeve to coil around his hand. The asp will bite any enemy the caster touches until it vanishes in 1 minute. The caster must make a melee attack roll, but the asp grants a +4 bonus. The attack roll can involve a normal melee attack</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">24-27</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\">Azi Dahaka sends a tangled mass of slithering snakes. The hissing swarm arrives in [[/roll 1d3]] rounds. The swarm occupies a space of 30&rsquo; x 30&rsquo; and attacks all enemies within that space. The individual snakes disperse after 1 minute. Snake swarm: Init +0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">28-29</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\">Azi Dahaka sends a brawny three-headed snake to aid his follower. It arrives in [[/roll 1d3]] rounds. The 20&rsquo; long creature obeys the caster&rsquo;s commands for 1 minute, then slithers away. Three-headed snake: Init +6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 102px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; height: 102px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">30-31</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 102px;\" align=\"left\">A spectral hydra shimmers into existence like a mirage above the sands. Its seven heads bite and breathe flame on the caster&rsquo;s enemies before vanishing on the following round. The caster may immediately direct seven attacks to any targets within 60&rsquo; of himself. Each attack is either a bite (+10 attack, [[/roll 4d6]] damage) or a fiery breath weapon (+15 attack, [[/roll 2d6]] damage plus DC 20 Ref save or target catches fire, suffering additional [[/roll 2d6]] damage each round until the target makes a DC 20 Ref save).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">32-500</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Azi Dahaka sends a spectral hydra, as above, which lasts for [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds. The caster may direct 7 attacks on each round it remains. The caster must concentrate to direct these attacks</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.36417%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-11</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.3485%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Failure. Unlike other spells, invoke patron may not be lost for the day. Depending on the Results of patron bond, the wizard may still be able to cast it.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>PATRON TAINT: AZI DAHAKA</h2>\n<p>When patron taint is indicated for Azi Dahaka, roll [[/roll 1d6]] on the table below. When a caster has acquired all six taints at all levels of effect, there is no need to continue rolling any more.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.dshmsEpriCQbT5bl]{Patron Taint: Azi Dahaka}@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.LcIOsjt1ph7scO5n]{Patron Taint: Azi Dahaka}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"34\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"3378\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1-1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">Casting any spell produces a light coat of fine dust, which settles over everything within 20&rsquo; of the caster</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">The caster&rsquo;s spells draw destructive storms of unnatural wrath. There is a 10% chance after casting any spell that thunder booms somewhere in the distance. If the Result is rolled a second time, any time the caster casts a spell, there is a 35% chance it is following by the immediate crash of localized thunder in [[/roll 1d5]] seconds. If the result is rolled a third time, there is a 50% chance that any spell causes a flash of lightning and the immediate crack of thunder. Those within 20&rsquo; of the caster must succeed on a DC 10 Fort save of be deafened for [[/roll 1d4]] rounds.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3-3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">The caster&rsquo;s presence brings ruin and decay to all things. Wooden and paper objects decay at his touch, crumbling into ash after a single week. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster&rsquo;s touch reduces cloth and leather to rags and then ash, after only ten days. If the result is rolled a third time, the caster&rsquo;s touch causes metal to rust and decay, crumbling into sand in a month&rsquo;s time. Magical objects resist the caster&rsquo;s casual touch, but still show wear where previously there was none, becoming pitted, mottled and worn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4-4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">Patches of the caster&rsquo;s torso skin peel away to reveal iridescent scales. If the Result is rolled a second time, the skin on the caster&rsquo;s arms and legs is transformed into scales. If the result is rolled a third time, the caster&rsquo;s skin molts, revealing a body covered by scales.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">5-5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">The caster&rsquo;s wounds weep clear ooze&mdash; an offering to Azi Dahaka that leaves the caster parched and dry. Anytime the caster takes a wound, he loses 1 additional hp due to the seeping ooze. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster develops weeping sores on his body</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.06781%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">6-6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.6448%;\" align=\"left\">The caster takes on the aspect of Azi Dahaka, as a second pair of eyes buds somewhere on his shoulders or back. A ruin mutation, the eyes are blind, but blink disconcertingly every few moments. If the Result is rolled a second time, two more sets of eyes bud somewhere on the caster&rsquo;s shoulders and back. If the result is rolled a third time, the budding faces fully emerge from the caster&rsquo;s body. The mouths moan strange dirges to Azi Dahaka in forgotten tongues, the nostrils flare wildly, and the blind eyes dart about unpredictably, as if tracking unseen beings.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>PATRON SPELLS: AZI DAHAKA</h2>\n<p>The demon prince of storms and waste grants three unique spells, as follows:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Level 1: @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-patron.2eqcjHEdFyw9FJxT]{Snake Trick}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Level 2: @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-patron.U1fmD8sXt7QAmaj4]{Kith of the Hydra}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Level 3: @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-patron.T1zxYkNcHuGaN6vY]{Reap the Whirlwind}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>SPELLBURN: AZI DAHAKA</h2>\n<p>Azi Dahaka enjoys the wailing cries of his devotees and often encourages even non-followers to call out to him in their times of distress. When a caster utilizes spellburn, roll [[/roll 1d4]] on the table below or build off the ideas below to create an event specific to your home campaign.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.eS7ASAYPDvsezFw9]{Spellburn: Azi Dahaka}@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spellburn-actions.XWfHFMLTnc10LZVW]{Azi Dahaka Spellburn Actions}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"34\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"2169\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 8.53739%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.7443%;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 8.53739%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1-1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.7443%;\" align=\"left\">The power of the spellburn opens the caster to the maddening horrors of the universe and leaves him weak (expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss) and disoriented. The caster must succeed on a DC 15 Will save or be unable to cast spells for [[/roll 1d3]] rounds. If the caster succeeds on the save, the caster gains a +1 bonus to all future attempts at the spell.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 8.53739%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.7443%;\" align=\"left\">Admiring the caster&rsquo;s ambition, Sezrekan grants the caster the opportunity to burn an ally&rsquo;s attributes (Stamina, Strength or Agility) in place of his own. The target must be willing. For every point burned to augment the spell, the target loses [[/roll 1d3]] points of the same attribute. If any of the target&rsquo;s attributes fall to 0 or less, the target dies.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 8.53739%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3-3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.7443%;\" align=\"left\">Sezrekan mocks the caster&rsquo;s feeble grasps at power. The caster receives but 1 point for every 2 points of attribute burned.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 8.53739%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4-4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.7443%;\" align=\"left\">Horrific madness seizes the caster&rsquo;s mind, and the awful meaninglessness of the universe is driven deep into his mortal soul. The caster is granted a single DC 15 Will save</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br /><br /></p>"}
{"_id":"r3Ze8N9Wugk8A4ci","name":"Turning Unholy","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.KHBxU22QxKfmGZLv"}},"content":"<p>pg. 96</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">By wielding his holy symbol and uttering holy words, a cleric can turn away the enemies of his faith. A cleric can attempt to turn away un-dead, demons, and devils. Some clerics of particular faiths may be able to turn away other kinds of creatures, depending on what powers their deities award them.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">A turn check is mechanically similar to a spell check, except that Luck matters. A d20 is rolled and added to the cleric&rsquo;s caster level. The cleric&rsquo;s Personality and Luck modifiers are also included. Compare the result of the turn check to @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.1yzqeGosJrlRGTWd]{Table 4-4: Turn Unholy Result by HD}.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">Turrned monsters usually receive a Will save to resist being turned. The save is made against the cleric&rsquo;s turn check. At sufficiently high results, a cleric may turn groups of weaker creatures automatically; they do not receive a saving throw.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">A failed turn check increases the cleric&rsquo;s range of natural disapproval, just as with a failed spell check.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">If a cleric raises his holy symbol to turn a group of mixed creatures, the player should indicate a specific target. Apply the results of the turn check based on the HD of the target creature. &ldquo;Overflow&rdquo; HD affect lower-HD creatures at the indicated effect. For example, if a cleric were charged by a band of 1 HD skeletons led by a 4 HD vampire commander, the player could designate whether he targets the skeletons or the vampire. If he targets the skeletons and his check is 19, he turns [[/roll 1d4]]+CL of these lesser un-dead but does not affect the vampire. If he targets the vampire and his next check is 24, he turns [[/roll 1d3]]+CL 4 HD creatures. If he rolls 5, that means he could turn the vampire and 4 of the skeletons.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\"><strong> </strong></p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.3982%; height: 187px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6882%; height: 17px; text-align: center;\" colspan=\"10\"><strong>Table 4-4: Turn Unholy Result in HD</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 4.46014%; height: 17px;\">Check</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.01884%; height: 17px;\">Turn Range</td>\n<td style=\"width: 14.4736%; height: 17px;\">Holy Smite</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6455%; height: 17px;\">1 HD</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6438%; height: 17px;\">2 HD</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.856%; height: 17px;\">3-4 HD</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">5-6 HD</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">7-8 HD</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27649%; height: 17px;\">9-10 HD</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.75749%; height: 17px;\">11-12 HD</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 4.46014%; height: 17px;\">1-11</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.01884%; height: 17px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 14.4736%; height: 17px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6455%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6438%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.856%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27649%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.75749%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 4.46014%; height: 17px;\">12-13</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.01884%; height: 17px;\">30'</td>\n<td style=\"width: 14.4736%; height: 17px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6455%; height: 17px;\">T1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6438%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.856%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27649%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.75749%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 4.46014%; height: 17px;\">14-17</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.01884%; height: 17px;\">30'</td>\n<td style=\"width: 14.4736%; height: 17px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6455%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d3]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6438%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.856%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27649%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.75749%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 4.46014%; height: 17px;\">18-19</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.01884%; height: 17px;\">30'</td>\n<td style=\"width: 14.4736%; height: 17px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6455%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d4]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6438%; height: 17px;\">T1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.856%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27649%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.75749%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 4.46014%; height: 17px;\">20-23</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.01884%; height: 17px;\">60'</td>\n<td style=\"width: 14.4736%; height: 17px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6455%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d6]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6438%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d3]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.856%; height: 17px;\">T1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27649%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.75749%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 4.46014%; height: 17px;\">24-27</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.01884%; height: 17px;\">60'</td>\n<td style=\"width: 14.4736%; height: 17px;\">Beam, 60', [[/roll 1d3]] dmg</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6455%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d8]]+CL, D[[/roll 1d4]] (no save)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6438%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d4]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.856%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d3]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">T1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27649%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.75749%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 4.46014%; height: 17px;\">28-29</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.01884%; height: 17px;\">60'</td>\n<td style=\"width: 14.4736%; height: 17px;\">Cone, 30', [[/roll 1d4]] dmg</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6455%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 2d6]]+CL, D[[/roll 1d4]] (no save)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6438%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d6]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.856%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d6]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d4]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">T1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27649%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.75749%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 4.46014%; height: 17px;\">30-31</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.01884%; height: 17px;\">120'</td>\n<td style=\"width: 14.4736%; height: 17px;\">Cone, 60', [[/roll 1d5]] dmg</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6455%; height: 17px;\">K[[/roll 1d8]]+CL (no save)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6438%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d8]]+CL, D[[/roll 1d4]] (no save)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.856%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d6]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d4]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d3]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27649%; height: 17px;\">T1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.75749%; height: 17px;\">NE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 4.46014%; height: 17px;\">32+</td>\n<td style=\"width: 8.01884%; height: 17px;\">240'</td>\n<td style=\"width: 14.4736%; height: 17px;\">Cone, 120', [[/roll 1d6]] dmg</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6455%; height: 17px;\">K[[/roll 2d6]]+CL (no save)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 17.6438%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 2d6]]+CL, D[[/roll 1d4]] (no save)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.856%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d8]]+CL, D[[/roll 1d4]]</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d6]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27817%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d4]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.27649%; height: 17px;\">T[[/roll 1d3]]+CL</td>\n<td style=\"width: 6.75749%; height: 17px;\">T1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>NE </strong>= No Effect.</p>\n<p><br /><strong>T </strong>= Creatures up to this HD are turned in a quantity indicated. For example, &ldquo;T1&rdquo; means one creature is turned; &ldquo;T[[/roll 1d4]]+CL&rdquo; means a number of creatures of this HD are turned equal to [[/roll 1d4]] + caster level. Unless indicated, turned creatures&nbsp; eceive a saving throw (Will vs. turn check DC). A turned creature moves away from the cleric at maximum speed or cowers if unable to retreat. A turned creature continues to flee for [[/roll 3d10]] minutes.</p>\n<p><br /><strong>D</strong> = Creatures are turned, and they take the indicated damage on the first round of turning. For example, T[[/roll 1d4]]+CL, D[[/roll 1d4]] means the cleric can turn a number of creatures of this HD equal to [[/roll 1d4]]+CL, and those creatures also take [[/roll 1d4]]<br />damage.</p>\n<p><br /><strong>K </strong>= Creatures are automatically killed. The number of creatures killed is indicated after the K. For example, K[[/roll 1d8]]+CL means the cleric kills a number of creatures of that HD equal to [[/roll 1d8]] + caster level.</p>\n<p><br /><strong>Holy Smite </strong>= At high levels, a cleric&rsquo;s turn attempt produces holy energy that smites unholy creatures in close proximity. This is in addition to the turning effect and can be directed in the same direction as the cleric&rsquo;s line-of-sight for the turning attempt. The effect and range varies, as described below, and all unholy creatures affected take the indicated damage automatically with no save. The damage occurs once per turn attempt; another turn check is required the&nbsp; following round to attempt again. Beam: a concentrated ray of light that the cleric can direct against one target within 60&rsquo;. Cone: a cone 30&rsquo; long and 30&rsquo; wide at its end.</p>"}
{"_id":"rNHV9QsvKtkH5QTO","name":"Combat Activities","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.gT8UF0P9x1URGyDU"}},"content":"<p>pg. 78</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Activity</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Time</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Draw or sheathe a weapon</td>\n<td>1 action*</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Equip or drop a shield</td>\n<td>1 action*</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Open a door</td>\n<td>1 action*</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Light a torch or lantern</td>\n<td>1 action</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Uncork a potion or unfurl a scroll</td>\n<td>1 action</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Locate an item in a backpack</td>\n<td>1 action</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Stand up from a prone position</td>\n<td>1 action</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mount or dismount a steed</td>\n<td>1 action</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Read a scroll or drink a potion</td>\n<td>1 action</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">* Can be included as part of a movement action.</span> </em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"reLCF2fGmD9x1QWP","name":"The King of Elfland","permission":{"default":0,"l6YjvvzdQ7bk09DR":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.GLymn2cpaspHZR5Q"}},"content":"<p>Master of the verdant realm glimpsed only through sun-dappled groves, the mist of great waterfalls, and the moments of dusk and dawn, the King of Elfland rules all elf-kin from his throne of mist and ice. Fierce once roused, the white-bearded regent keeps watch over the dreaming land, protecting against incursion. He grants fearsome powers to his mortal champions, but can often seem fickle and sanguine, neglecting affairs not immediately pertaining to the Elflands.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>Invoke Patron</em> check results:</strong></p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-patron.4trndajEJGkqRqZd]{Invoke the King of Elfland}@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-patron.nUW4Jc3GzfHON3wx]{Invoke the King of Elfland}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%; height: 492px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"2813\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%; height: 16px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%; height: 16px;\" align=\"left\">Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (3 or less) @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.ulpbL6uovfl9Qr4Y]{Invoke the King of Elfland Corruption}+ @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.uZKHW8Xt4vWg096p]{Patron Taint: The King of Elfland}; (4-5) @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.ulpbL6uovfl9Qr4Y]{Invoke the King of Elfland Corruption}; (6+) @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.uZKHW8Xt4vWg096p]{Patron Taint: The King of Elfland}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-11</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Failure. Unlike other spells, invoke patron may not be lost for the day. Depending on the Results of patron bond, the wizard may still be able to cast it.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">12-13</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">The King of Elfland answers the petitioner's plea, but is quickly distracted by other matters. The caster receives +4 to his next attack, saving throw, skill check, or spell check.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">14-17</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\">The caster's weapons are endowed with the slumbering magic of Elfland. For the next [[/roll 1d5]]+CL rounds, targets struck by the caster's weapons must succeed on a DC 10+CL Will save or succumb to magical sleep (duration [[/roll 1d6]] hours; can only be roused by violent shaking for [[/roll 1d4]] rounds). The magic is associated with the caster&rsquo;s weapons not the caster; while the magic persists, another character may attack with these weapons to gain the same benefit.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">18-19</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\">For [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds, the caster fades from existence, becoming a mere shadow suspended between the fae realms and the mortal lands. His AC and Ref saves improve by +2, and with a successful Will save (DC 10), the caster can turn invisible. If the caster critically fails the Will save by rolling a natural 1, he delves too far into the Elflands, vanishing into the fae realms, never to return.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">20-23</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">The King of Elfland grants the caster a chance to step back in time [[/roll 1d6]]+CL rounds. This does not automatically change the flow of events that has already happened</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">24-27</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\">The caster's weapons are enchanted with the wrothful magic of Elfland. For the next [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds, targets struck by the caster's weapons must succeed on a DC 10+CL Will save or vanish into Elfland, returning to the mortal plane some [[/roll 5d10]]0 years later. Immortals and other extraplanar creatures (at the judge's discretion) may be immune to the caster's dread magics. The magic is associated with the caster's weapons not the caster</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">28-29</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">The King of Elfland grants the caster a chance to step back in time [[/roll 1d6]]+CL hours. This does not change the flow of events that has already happened</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">30-31</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\">The caster becomes a shining sylvan paladin in the service of Elfland. For [[/roll 1d8]]+CL rounds, the caster and three allies of his choosing receive +4 to AC and all saving throws, +3 to all attacks, spell check and damage rolls, and automatically succeed on any Recovering the Body checks.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 9.66121%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">32-500</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.0514%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\">The King of Elfland anoints the caster as his champion. For [[/roll 1d12]]+CL rounds, the caster and five allies of his choosing receive +6 to AC and all saving throws, +5 to all attacks, spell check and damage rolls, and automatically succeed on any Recovering the Body checks. Even if one of the characters is somehow slain, he simply slips into the sylvan realms where he is healed by elven maids, returning to the mortal realms [[/roll 1d3]] days later, healed in both body and soul.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>PATRON TAINT: THE KING OF ELFLAND</h2>\n<p>The King of Elfland is a vexing patron, indifferent and then demanding by turns. Those in his service must be dedicated to their liege and vengeful against his foes. Few can view the master of Elfland and not be influenced by his boundless lust for life.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>When a patron taint is indicated, roll [[/roll 1d6]] on the table below. When a caster has acquired all six taints at all levels of effect, there is no need to continue rolling any more.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.uZKHW8Xt4vWg096p]{Patron Taint: The King of Elfland}@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.DqI13jzKFwJztvFk]{Patron Taint: the King of Elfland}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"34\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"3292\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1-1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">The caster is seized by in explicable longing for the forests of Elfland and yearns to visit the mythic land. If the Result is rolled a second time, the longing overcomes the caster</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">The vibrant, verdant power of the Elflands seeps into the caster. The caster&rsquo;s skin takes on a green hue, especially at dusk and dawn. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster buds hints of velvet-covered antlers. If the result is rolled a third time, antlers sprout from the caster&rsquo;s forehead and his skin is covered in a soft coat of green-hued fur.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3-3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">The caster adopts the sanguine indifference of his patron. He becomes aloof and easily distracted, reducing his Personality by -1. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster becomes withdrawn from mortal concerns&mdash;the promise of gold and glory have little draw</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4-4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">Animals are inexplicably drawn to the caster. Though they do not obey the caster&rsquo;s commands (and, indeed, ignore the caster&rsquo;s attempts to shoo them), domesticated animals of every sort long to be within the caster&rsquo;s presence. If the Result is rolled a second time, the effect extends to small wild animals&mdash; birds, rats and the like&mdash;which accompany the PC wherever he goes. If the result is rolled a third time, the caster cannot go anywhere without being accosted by animals of all sort.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">5-5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">The caster sees sprites and the like out of the corner of his vision and just out of sight. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster comes to the very visceral realization that the entire world is alive with spirits and finds himself absent-mindedly consulting them when challenges arise. If the result is rolled a third time, his perception of the natural world of the spirit is far more real than the usual mortal realm, and the caster must make an effort (Will save, DC 15) in order to interact with mortals during anything other than life-threatening situations.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">6-6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">The caster is easily distracted and struggles to stay focused on the present: The judge may select a single spell that takes 1 round to cast</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>SPELLBURN: THE KING OF ELFLAND</h2>\n<p>The King of Elfland readily lends his strength to his champions, but few are those that can hold their master&rsquo;s attention for long. Those that do hope to win their patron&rsquo;s support must be cunning, clever and courageous. When a caster utilizes spellburn, roll [[/roll 1d4]] and consult the table below or build off the suggestions to create an event specific to your home campaign.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.tr7yFfH8ujaOrXOE]{Spellburn: The King of Elfland} @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spellburn-actions.KbEH1sdTqyydpaXj]{The King of Elfland Spellburn Actions}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup span=\"2\" width=\"85\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.42271%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.2899%;\" align=\"left\">A fearsome, scintillating dragon appears over the caster&rsquo;s shoulder. As the spellburn takes effect, the dragon is drawn into the caster, the shock of the effect manifesting as stat point loss.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.42271%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.2899%;\" align=\"left\">The caster is granted the spellburn bonus, but must succeed on a minor quest in the next [[/roll 1d4]] weeks; until the quest is completed, the caster cannot regain the burned stat points. The goal of the quest is both trivial and difficult&mdash;typically to recover an item with a value only understood by the King of Elfland: a dwarven smith&rsquo;s favorite anvil; the tiara of a lady-in-waiting; the Black Knight&rsquo;s shield; the Emperor of the World&rsquo;s favorite diadem.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.42271%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.2899%;\" align=\"left\">Calling on the sylvan realm causes a bit of the caster&rsquo;s shadow to leave for an errand in the Elflands; forcing one&rsquo;s own shadow away requires great mental force, manifesting as stat loss.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.42271%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.2899%;\" align=\"left\">In order to succeed on the spellburn, the caster must come up with a pun, riddle or rhyme that delights the King of Elfland. If the King is amused, the PC need not spend any attribute points for the spellburn, but if the King is less than delighted, the caster must pay twice as many stat points for the burn.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>PATRON SPELLS: THE KING OF ELFLAND</h2>\n<p>The King of Elfland grants three unique spells, as follows:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Level 1: @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-patron.xRZHZGhyNQLwarbH]{Forest Walk}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Level 2: @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-patron.YgnarKaEubQBv6YQ]{War Horn of Elfland}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Level 3: @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-patron.wmeJgf0oj8FjhIDn]{The Dreaming}</p>\n<p><br /><br /></p>"}
{"_id":"rimsNot2JSYyfwNr","name":"Getting Started","permission":{"default":0,"l6YjvvzdQ7bk09DR":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.gp3fbe1PiPMiHgqS"}},"content":"<h1>Getting Started with the Dungeon Crawl Classics Core Book</h1>\n<p>Welcome to the DCC Core Book compendiums for FoundryVTT!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Where are all my compendiums? How do I import them?</h2>\n<p>We provide a lot of data from the core book in the form of compendiums. To get to your compendiums, look for the Book/Atlas icon <img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/compendium.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"18\" height=\"23\" /> labelled Compendium Packs at the top right. You can also just import them when you start using the core book module. Click the Import Content button on the welcome screen, select what you want to import, and the system will import the compendium content into your world. This may make it easier for you to find stuff.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Here's a list of what you get:</p>\n<p>All NPCs from the core book as <strong>Actors <img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/actors.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"23\" height=\"23\" />: </strong>Cyclopedia of Creatures Monstrous and Mundane, Men and Magicians</p>\n<p>All gear from the core book as <strong>Items <img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/items.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"26\" height=\"23\" />: </strong>Ammunition, Armor, Equipment, Mounts, Weapons</p>\n<p>All Spells from the core book as <strong>Items </strong><strong><strong><img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/items.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"26\" height=\"23\" /></strong>:</strong> Cleric, Wizard, Patron Spells by level or Patron. These are the objects you will drag onto a Wizard, Elf, or Cleric who wants to cast them.</p>\n<p>All text from the core book as <strong>Journal <img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/journal.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"27\" height=\"22\" /></strong> entries. These come in two forms:<strong> Core Book Text,</strong> which is just a set of chapters straight from the book with tables. You also get <strong>Core Book Journals, </strong>which is a searchable set of journal entries on main topics from the book that are more suitable for reference or sharing with players.</p>\n<p>All monsters from the core book as <strong>Journal </strong><strong><img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/journal.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"27\" height=\"22\" /></strong> entries. The journal entries for Cyclopedia of Creatures Monstrous and Mundane and Men and Magicians provide the core text for the monster as well as any tables for the monster, and links to the monster <strong>Actor.</strong></p>\n<p>Indices of the core text as <strong>Journal </strong><strong><strong><img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/journal.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"27\" height=\"22\" /></strong> </strong>entries. These are handy lists of content by subject that may help you find stuff.</p>\n<p>All spell tables from the core book as <strong>Journal </strong><strong><strong><img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/journal.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"27\" height=\"22\" /></strong> </strong> entries. This will allow you to browse spell results in an easy to read manner.</p>\n<p>All spell result, manifestation, corruption, and misfire tables as <strong>RollTable</strong> <img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/table.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"27\" height=\"24\" /> entries. These are linked to spell entries that you will be assigning to player characters - you shouldn't need to use them manually. But they are there in case you want to modify results.</p>\n<p>All core book tables as <strong>RollTable </strong><img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/table.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"27\" height=\"24\" /> entries. This includes anything from Luck Score, to Mercurial Magic, to Crits and Fumbles. You won't need to set up Crits and Fumbles or Disapproval for yourself if you own this module. You just need to have them entered correctly on your character sheet (i.e. IV for Crit Table). The same is true of spell results: you won't need to set up spell results if you have this module, as long as you drag the spell's <strong>Item </strong>to your sheet. You will need to click Manfiestation, Misfire, or Corruption if you wish to roll those, but they are rollable from the chat window when you cast a spell.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Where is the user guide?</h2>\n<p>The User Guide comes with the base system. It is in the <strong>Journals </strong>section of the compendiums. You can import it from the welcome dialog, which will also place it in your <strong>Journals </strong><strong><strong><img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/journal.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"27\" height=\"22\" /></strong>.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Is there an Index?</h2>\n<p>Yes. After you import, an Index folder will be added to your <strong>Journals </strong><strong><strong><img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/journal.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"27\" height=\"22\" /></strong></strong>. It is also in the Index compendium.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Adding gear, spells, etc. by dragging from a compendium.</h2>\n<p>All the gear, spells, critical hits, etc. are taken care of for you. If you want to give a character a spell, just drag it from the&nbsp;<strong>Items</strong> <strong><strong><img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/items.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"26\" height=\"23\" /> </strong></strong>folder that contains what you want. For example, if your Wizard wants the Sleep spell, click <strong>Items</strong> <strong><strong><img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/items.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"26\" height=\"23\" /></strong></strong>, Wizard Spells Level 1, and just drag it ionto your character sheet. Then you can just click the icon next to your spell to cast it (and even drag the icon to your macro bar to cast it from there). You can even roll Mercurial Magic for the spell by clicking the Pencil <strong><strong><img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/pencil.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"22\" height=\"22\" /> </strong></strong>icon next to the spell, then clicking the Roll button next to Mercurual Magic.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>It works the same way for Weapons, Equipment, Mounts, or Armor.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>How can I submit bugs, suggestions, or feature requests?</h2>\n<p>As long as you have installed and enabled the Bug Reporter module, click the <strong>Game Settings </strong><strong><strong><img src=\"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/webp/dcc-core-icons/gear.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"26\" height=\"23\" /></strong></strong> icon in the top right and click Post Bug. That will allow you to select a module and submit a bug, suggestion, or request.</p>"}
