{"_id":"slgT7FdCkK31RpSP","name":"Table 5-3: Minor Corruption","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L6xS9Qmd3y4hU1WP"}},"content":"<p>pg. 116</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-tables.ZuGmhXGbhrJIuX9v]{Table 5-3: Minor Corruption}</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"85\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"369\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>d10</strong></td>\n<td align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1 or lower</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Character develops horrid pustules on his face. These pustules do not heal and impose a -1 penalty to Personality.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Character&rsquo;s skin on one random portion of his body appears to melt. Like wax, it flows and reforms into odd puddles and shapes. This is an ongoing, constant motion that itches constantly and repulses others. Determine location randomly ([[/roll 1d6]]): (1) face; (2) arms; (3) legs; (4) torso; (5) hands; (6) feet.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3</td>\n<td align=\"left\">One of the character&rsquo;s legs grows [[/roll 1d6]]&rdquo;. Character now walks with an odd gait.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Eyes affected. Roll [[/roll 1d4]]: (1) eyes glow with unearthly color; (2) eyes gain light sensitivity (-1 to all rolls in daylight); (3) character gains infravision (sees heat signatures at range of 100&rsquo;); (4) eyes become large and unblinking, like a fish.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">5</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Character develops painful lesions on his chest and legs and open sores on his hands and feet that do not heal.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">6</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Ears mutate. Roll [[/roll 1d5]]: (1) ears become pointed; (2) ears fall off (character still hears normally); (3) ears enlarge and look like an elephant&rsquo;s; (4) ears elongate and look like a donkey&rsquo;s (character also gains braying laugh); (5) ears shrivel and fold back.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">7</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Chills. Character shakes constantly and cannot remain quiet due to chattering teeth.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">8</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Character&rsquo;s facial appearance is permanently disfigured according to the magic that was summoned. If fire magic was used, his eyebrows are scorched and his skin glows red; if cold magic was used, his skin is pasty white and his lips are blue. If ambiguous magic was used, his appearance grows gaunt and he permanently loses 5 pounds.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">9</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Character&rsquo;s hair is suffused with dark energy. Roll [[/roll 1d4]]: (1) hair turns bone white; (2) hair turns pitch black; (3) hair falls out completely; (4) hair sticks straight up.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">10+</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Character passes out. He is unconscious for [[/roll 1d6]] hours or until awakened by vigorous means.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
{"_id":"tmxL3ueMFz0Urol2","name":"Sezrekan","permission":{"default":0,"l6YjvvzdQ7bk09DR":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.wudaii5glqiwalBd"}},"content":"<p>pg. 336</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Regarded as the wickedest of wizards ever to plague the Known World, Sezrekan the Elder was born to a peasant family and cursed with the knowledge of higher worlds. Straining to hear the music of the heavenly spheres, the aspiring wizard found only chaos and madness. Forsaking patron and liege alike, Sezrekan sought to free himself of the world and his mortal coil, regardless of the cost. Those who claim him as their patron are expected to follow in the Master&rsquo;s footsteps, sacrificing kith and kin in the single-minded pursuit of mastery of self and thereby the multiverse. The Old Master has little regard for those that cannot help themselves, offering his aid only to spellcasters of proven dedication and talent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>Invoke Patron</em> check results:</strong></p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.qslx9RarpJfHDSwC]{Invoke Sezrekan}@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-patron.cGJMuI6JU7ZWpNL1]{Invoke Sezrekan}</p>\n<table style=\"height: 407px; width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"49\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"2903\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 11.6854%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 88.0273%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 11.6854%; height: 16px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88.0273%; height: 16px;\" align=\"left\">Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (3 or less) @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.eLkFO5wJP3TtHIju]{Invoke Sezrekan Corruption}+ @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.bsWbWYOywjkoLrgP]{Patron Taint: Sezrekan}; (4-5) @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.eLkFO5wJP3TtHIju]{Invoke Sezrekan Corruption}; (6+) @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.bsWbWYOywjkoLrgP]{Patron Taint: Sezrekan}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 11.6854%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-11</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88.0273%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Failure. Unlike other spells, invoke patron may not be lost for the day. Depending on the Results of patron bond, the wizard may still be able to cast it.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 85px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 11.6854%; height: 85px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">12-13</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88.0273%; height: 85px;\" align=\"left\">Sezrekan cannot be troubled by such an insignificant petitioner. He grants the caster an additional [[/roll 6d4]] hit points. These may be burned in spellburn, with every 4 hp equaling a point of attribute. At the end of the hour, all the extra hit points are lost. Damage and spellburn are deducted first from the additional hit points. For example, a caster that is granted 16 hit points and takes 14 points of damage in the hour, would then lose only the 2 remaining hit points when the duration expires.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 11.6854%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">14-17</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88.0273%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Sezrekan teleports the caster to a location [[/roll 1d10]]0 miles distant. The caster cannot choose the location, but is not in immediate danger upon his arrival.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 11.6854%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">18-19</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88.0273%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Sezrekan permits the caster to recall a previously lost spell.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 11.6854%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">20-23</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88.0273%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\">Sezrekan notes the caster&rsquo;s potential talent, granting +5 to the caster&rsquo;s next spell check.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 11.6854%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">24-27</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88.0273%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Sezrekan teleports the caster and up to 8 allies to a location [[/roll 5d10]]0 miles distant. The caster cannot choose the location, but the party is not in immediate peril upon their arrival.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 11.6854%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">28-29</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88.0273%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Sezrekan is impressed by the caster&rsquo;s might and deigns to grant a total of +10 to the caster&rsquo;s next two spell checks. The points can be allotted as the caster sees fit, but must be declared prior to the castings.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 11.6854%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">30-31</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88.0273%; height: 51px;\" align=\"left\">A phantasmal specter of Sezrekan appears, raining down hellfire on those that would dare challenge such a talented adept. Meteors and comets fall streaking from the sky, striking any foes within 50&rsquo; for [[/roll 3d8]] damage (Ref save vs. spell check to avoid). The rain of fire continues for [[/roll 1d3]] rounds.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 11.6854%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">32-500</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88.0273%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\">Sezrekan recognizes the caster as a peer (albeit, a lesser peer) worthy of his aid in their shared efforts to cast off the shackles of an uncaring universe. He grants a total bonus of +30 to the caster&rsquo;s next five spell checks. The points can be allotted as the caster sees fit (up to +10 per spell check), but the allotment must be declared prior to the casting.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>PATRON TAINT: SEZREKAN</h2>\n<p>Whereas other patrons scar their petitioners with foul taints, followers of the Old Master inflict injuries on themselves while in pursuit of the Sezrekan&rsquo;s mastery of magic. When patron taint is indicated, roll [[/roll 1d6]] on the table below. When a caster has acquired all six taints at all levels of effect, there is no need to continue rolling any more.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.aFRNiBtY6fbXqZ0I]{Patron Taint: Sezrekan}@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.bsWbWYOywjkoLrgP]{Patron Taint: Sezrekan}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%; height: 554px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"34\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"4020\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.90386%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.8088%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 119px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.90386%; height: 119px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1-1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.8088%; height: 119px;\" align=\"left\">Incited to madness and brimming with occult knowledge, the caster spends his next action carving a third eye into his forehead (inflicting [[/roll 1d3]] points of damage in the process). Upon return to civilization, the caster seeks out a tattooist who inks a third eye on the caster&rsquo;s forehead using exotic inks costing no less than [[/roll 1d5]] x 100 gp. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster insists on wearing a blindfold for the next [[/roll 1d4]] days, in the earnest hope of awakening his third eye. If the result is rolled a third time, the caster stabs a dagger into each of his real eyes, blinding himself. (There is a 3% chance, per level, that the self-mutilation brings the PC&rsquo;s third eye to life.)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 119px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.90386%; height: 119px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.8088%; height: 119px;\" align=\"left\">Dazzled by his new insight into the terrifying nature of the multiverse, the caster is spurred into offering up sacrifices in thanks to the Old Master. The caster is driven to enact the ritual as soon as it is reasonably safe, though the caster&rsquo;s threat assessment may not agree with that of his peers. In a ritual lasting 1 turn, the caster offers up wealth totaling at least [[/roll 1d5]] x 100 gp in honor of Sezrekan. All the items are consumed in searing blue flames, and there is a 3% chance that Sezrekan honors the sacrifice with a +1 bonus to the caster&rsquo;s next spell check. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster must sacrifice a magic item</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 102px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.90386%; height: 102px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3-3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.8088%; height: 102px;\" align=\"left\">In a passing moment of d&eacute;j&agrave; vu, the caster realizes that Sezrekan demands his service. Subject to the judge&rsquo;s discretion, the caster must adventure to retrieve an occult item or lost relic for the Old Master, located within [[/roll 1d4]] days travel. The caster has a clear vision of the item, but only a rough sense of its location and wards. If the Result is rolled a second time, the item is well warded and some [[/roll 1d4]] weeks distant. If the result is rolled a third time, the item is guarded by ancient wards, traps, and fiends, requiring [[/roll 1d4]] months of dangerous travel.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 102px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.90386%; height: 102px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4-4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.8088%; height: 102px;\" align=\"left\">In a lucid dream of mighty Sezrekan, the caster realizes his own spells are terribly flawed and dependent on the aid of outsiders. Forsaking their influence, the caster gives up a known first level spell, vowing to never cast it again. (If, later, the caster discovers another spell of the same level, it can take the place of the original spell among the caster&rsquo;s known spells.) If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster must surrender a second level spell. If the result is rolled a third time, the caster must surrender a third level spell. Should the caster refuse to give up any of the spells, he forsakes Sezrekan as his patron.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 85px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.90386%; height: 85px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">5-5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.8088%; height: 85px;\" align=\"left\">The daunting scope of the caster&rsquo;s knowledge induces a creeping madness that begins to seep into his everyday life. The caster must declare a common substance (iron, water, steel, cotton, gold, silver, silk, wood, leather, velum, meat, etc.) and declare it taboo. Henceforth, the caster makes every effort to avoid contact with the taboo substance. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster must choose a second taboo</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 10px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.90386%; height: 10px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">6-6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.8088%; height: 10px;\" align=\"left\">The caster is caught up in a dream world of hallucinations for the next [[/roll 1d5]] rounds, as a spectral image of Sezrekan strides through his vision. The caster can still interact with the real world, but if he chooses to ignore his surroundings and watch only the Old Master, he gleans hints and indications of Sezrekan&rsquo;s dweomercaft mastery. If the caster spends the next [[/roll 1d4]] days in solitary research, he is able to learn a new spell of his choosing. Failing to immediately retire to study causes the insights to be lost, like the fading memory of a dream. This Result can be rolled up to three times.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>PATRON SPELLS: SEZREKAN</h2>\n<p>Those daring to follow of the Path of the Mad Mage eventually learn three unique spells, as follows:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Level 1: @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.y3Gj0ztSCEDlOv0d]{Sequester}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Level 2: @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.rjrJPR0tcfiS20N3]{Shield Maiden}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Level 3: @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.l3OQA5cpkuSvu1Vg]{Phylactery of the Soul}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>SPELLBURN: SEZREKAN</h2>\n<p>Sezrekan does little to aid his followers. Those that are strong and willful distinguish themselves by their might, while the weak and pitiful are worthless tools to be discarded. And yet, the Old Master has been known to admire those that sacrifice their own bodies in pursuit of the impossible. When a caster utilizes spellburn, roll [[/roll 1d4]] and consult the table below or build off the suggestions to create an event specific to your home campaign.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.ozxzqhAVK2QxIs9j]{Spellburn: Sezrekan} @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spellburn-actions.YanqOfsEBkofHpn6]{Sezrekan Spellburn Actions}</p>\n<table style=\"height: 221px; width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"34\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"2169\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.33249%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.3801%; height: 17px;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.33249%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1-1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.3801%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\">The power of the spellburn opens the caster to the maddening horrors of the universe and leaves him weak (expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss) and disoriented. The caster must succeed on a DC 15 Will save or be unable to cast spells for [[/roll 1d3]] rounds. If the caster succeeds on the save, the caster gains a +1 bonus to all future attempts at the spell.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.33249%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.3801%; height: 68px;\" align=\"left\">Admiring the caster&rsquo;s ambition, Sezrekan grants the caster the opportunity to burn an ally&rsquo;s attributes (Stamina, Strength or Agility) in place of his own. The target must be willing. For every point burned to augment the spell, the target loses [[/roll 1d3]] points of the same attribute. If any of the target&rsquo;s attributes fall to 0 or less, the target dies.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.33249%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3-3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.3801%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Sezrekan mocks the caster&rsquo;s feeble grasps at power. The caster receives but 1 point for every 2 points of attribute burned.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 7.33249%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4-4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 92.3801%; height: 34px;\" align=\"left\">Horrific madness seizes the caster&rsquo;s mind, and the awful meaninglessness of the universe is driven deep into his mortal soul. The caster is granted a single DC 15 Will save</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br /><br /></p>"}
{"_id":"tr7yFfH8ujaOrXOE","name":"Spellburn: The King of Elfland","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.9bKjGe3qAJlsAaAf"}},"content":"<p>pg. 344<br /><br /></p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spellburn-actions.KbEH1sdTqyydpaXj]{The King of Elfland Spellburn Actions}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.42271%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.2899%;\" align=\"left\">A fearsome, scintillating dragon appears over the caster&rsquo;s shoulder. As the spellburn takes effect, the dragon is drawn into the caster, the shock of the effect manifesting as stat point loss.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.42271%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.2899%;\" align=\"left\">The caster is granted the spellburn bonus, but must succeed on a minor quest in the next [[/roll 1d4]] weeks; until the quest is completed, the caster cannot regain the burned stat points. The goal of the quest is both trivial and difficult&mdash;typically to recover an item with a value only understood by the King of Elfland: a dwarven smith&rsquo;s favorite anvil; the tiara of a lady-in-waiting; the Black Knight&rsquo;s shield; the Emperor of the World&rsquo;s favorite diadem.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.42271%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.2899%;\" align=\"left\">Calling on the sylvan realm causes a bit of the caster&rsquo;s shadow to leave for an errand in the Elflands; forcing one&rsquo;s own shadow away requires great mental force, manifesting as stat loss.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.42271%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.2899%;\" align=\"left\">In order to succeed on the spellburn, the caster must come up with a pun, riddle or rhyme that delights the King of Elfland. If the King is amused, the PC need not spend any attribute points for the spellburn, but if the King is less than delighted, the caster must pay twice as many stat points for the burn.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
{"_id":"uZKHW8Xt4vWg096p","name":"Patron Taint: The King of Elfland","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.SSilP9chn4dDrILE"}},"content":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>pg. 343</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-effect-tables.DqI13jzKFwJztvFk]{Patron Taint: the King of Elfland}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1-1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">The caster is seized by in explicable longing for the forests of Elfland and yearns to visit the mythic land. If the Result is rolled a second time, the longing overcomes the caster</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">2-2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">The vibrant, verdant power of the Elflands seeps into the caster. The caster&rsquo;s skin takes on a green hue, especially at dusk and dawn. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster buds hints of velvet-covered antlers. If the result is rolled a third time, antlers sprout from the caster&rsquo;s forehead and his skin is covered in a soft coat of green-hued fur.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">3-3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">The caster adopts the sanguine indifference of his patron. He becomes aloof and easily distracted, reducing his Personality by -1. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster becomes withdrawn from mortal concerns&mdash;the promise of gold and glory have little draw</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">4-4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">Animals are inexplicably drawn to the caster. Though they do not obey the caster&rsquo;s commands (and, indeed, ignore the caster&rsquo;s attempts to shoo them), domesticated animals of every sort long to be within the caster&rsquo;s presence. If the Result is rolled a second time, the effect extends to small wild animals&mdash; birds, rats and the like&mdash;which accompany the PC wherever he goes. If the result is rolled a third time, the caster cannot go anywhere without being accosted by animals of all sort.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">5-5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">The caster sees sprites and the like out of the corner of his vision and just out of sight. If the Result is rolled a second time, the caster comes to the very visceral realization that the entire world is alive with spirits and finds himself absent-mindedly consulting them when challenges arise. If the result is rolled a third time, his perception of the natural world of the spirit is far more real than the usual mortal realm, and the caster must make an effort (Will save, DC 15) in order to interact with mortals during anything other than life-threatening situations.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 9.10639%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">6-6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90.6063%;\" align=\"left\">The caster is easily distracted and struggles to stay focused on the present: The judge may select a single spell that takes 1 round to cast; the caster must succeed on a DC 10 Will check or take an extra +[[/roll 1d3]] rounds to cast the spell. If the result is rolled a second time, the judge should choose a second spell; the caster must succeed on a DC 15 Will check or take an extra +[[/roll 1d3]] rounds to cast the spell. If the result is rolled a third time, the judge should choose a third spell; the caster must succeed on a DC 20 Will check or take an extra +[[/roll 1d3]] rounds to cast the spell.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
{"_id":"uxnbxBtH6EY6VNPr","name":"Table 9-1: Humanoid Skin Color","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.4qFq4EMAwja585Dp"}},"content":"<p>pg. 380</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-tables.kQVGhgDogcwvRTgx]{Table 9-1: Humanoid Skin Color}</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"100\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"511\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"23\"><strong>d20</strong></td>\n<td align=\"justify\"><strong>Skin Color</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">1</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Chalky white</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">2</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Albino</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">3</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Pitch black</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">4</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Dark gray</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">5</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Light gray</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">6</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Sky blue</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">7</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Navy blue</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">8</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Crimson red</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">9</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Bright red</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">10</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Yellow</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">11</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Orange</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">12</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Green</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">13</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Brown</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">14</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Purple</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">15</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Translucent</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">16</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Completely transpare</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">17</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Human skin tone</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">18</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Torso different than limbs; roll again twice, once for torso and once for limbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">19</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">Head different from body; roll again twice, once for head and once for body</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"justify\" height=\"17\">20</td>\n<td align=\"justify\">As per typical specimen of that type</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
{"_id":"vycwtEPfYdeQARUR","name":"Elf","permission":{"default":0,"l6YjvvzdQ7bk09DR":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.qD7JpRQSZUd66uoz"}},"content":"<p>pg. 56</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You are a strong, slender demi-human native to woodlands and shaded forests. You avoid the provincial oafs of the younger races, with their bumbling war-making and crude superstitions. Against the noisy backdrop of their empires rising, falling, and rising again, your magical enclaves advance the study of arts and crafts millennia in the making.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Elves live for more than a thousand years in small cities of like-minded individuals. Reproducing and maturing slowly, and likewise studying and practicing with great patience over many years, each elf masters his chosen area of expertise at a level of competency no man can hope to achieve. Those elves who study the martial or magical arts may find themselves in search of an arcane relic, a divine token, or a legendary weapon. These seekers comprise the rare elven adventurers encountered by humans.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Elves divide their race into castes not always evident to outsiders, each speaking specific sub-dialects of a common, ancient tongue. There are forest elves and plains-dwelling elves, undersea elves and elves who dwell on floating cloud-cities. A fallen race of black-skinned dark elves shuns the glare of sunlight.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Elven longevity, combined with their skill with magic, has created many legends about their racial roots. Whether elves really have traffic with demons and gods is for them to know and the other races to discover.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Elves can cast spells as wizards do. An elf of the same power level as a human wizard also has many decades of combat experience. As such, elves typically cast their spells just as competently as human wizards and also have martial skills.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Hit points:</strong> An elf gains [[/roll 1d6]] hit points at each level.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Weapon training:</strong> An elf is trained in the use of the dagger, javelin, lance, longbow, longsword, shortbow, short sword, staff, spear, and two-handed sword. Elves often wear armor of mithril, even though it affects their spellcasting.</p>\n<p>Because of their sensitivity to iron (as explained below), elf characters are trained from an early age with mithril weapons. Before they depart on a life of adventure, they have acquired mithril equipment. At 1st level, an elf character may purchase one piece of armor and one weapon that are manufactured of mithril at no additional cost. Mithril armor weighs slightly less than iron or steel armor of the same type and can be worn by the elf without the pain normally associated with metal armors.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Alignment:</strong> With their multicentenarian lifespan and proclivity for observation over action, elves tend toward chaotic and neutral alignments. Because they outlive many institutions of authority, elves are not often of lawful alignments.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Magic:</strong> Elves practice arcane magic sustained by traffic with otherworldly creatures. More so than human wizards, they form relationships with specific demi-beings and can directly request aid from beyond. Where a human wizard may cast a spell to summon a demon a few times in his life, an elf may converse repeatedly with the same demon so many times over so many centuries that long-term arrangements become feasible. All elveshave one or more extraplanar patrons who sustain their magic. As such, their spells tend more toward those associated with elemental or demonic powers.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Elf spells are determined randomly like a wizard&rsquo;s, except for invoke patron and patron bond, as described below.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Caster level:</strong> Caster level is a measurement of an elf&rsquo;s power in channeling a spell&rsquo;s energy. An elf&rsquo;s caster level is his level as an elf. For example, a 2nd-level elf has a caster level of 2.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Supernatural patrons:</strong> Like wizards, elves can invoke supernatural patrons. An elf automatically receives the spells patron bond and invoke patron at 1st level in addition to his other spells.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Infravision: </strong>An elf can see in thedark up to 60&rsquo;. @Compendium[dcc.dcc-userguide.ZEfUr57DcFyTPgEo]{Infravision &amp; Torches}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Immunities:</strong> Elves are immune to magical sleep and paralysis.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Vulnerabilities:</strong> Elves are extremely sensitive to the touch of iron. Direct contact over prolonged periods causes a burning sensation, and exposure at close distances makes them uncomfortable. An elf may not wear iron armor or bear the touch of iron weapons for extended periods. Prolonged contact with iron causes 1 hp of damage per day of direct contact.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Heightened Senses: </strong>Elves are astute and observant. All elf characters receive a +4 bonus to detect secret doors. Moreover, when simply passing within 10 feet of a secret door, elves are entitled to a check to detect it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Luck:</strong> With their long lifespan, elves have ample opportunity to practice their magic craft. At first level, an elf may choose to apply his Luck modifier to spell checks on one spell of his choosing. That modifier does not change as the elf&rsquo;s Luck score changes.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Languages:</strong> At 1st-level, an elf automatically knows Common, the elven racial language, and one other language. An elf knows one additional language for every point of Int modifier. Additional languages are randomly determined as specified in Appendix L.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Action dice: </strong>An elf&rsquo;s action dice can be used for attacks or spell checks at any level. At 5th level, an elf can cast two spells in a single round, the first with a d20 spell check and the second with a d14; or he can make two attacks, the first with a d20 attack roll and the second with a d14; or he may combine an attack with a spell check. Note that the results of mercurial magic supersede the action dice, so an elf with a particularly high (or low) spell check die from mercurial magic uses that result instead (with his total actions still limited by his level).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.IQ1SpPEUWkIgxgZF]{Table 1-16: Elf}</p>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" colspan=\"9\"><strong>Table 1-16: Elf</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Level</p>\n</td>\n<td>Attack</td>\n<td>Crit Die/Table</td>\n<td>Action Dice</td>\n<td>Known Spells*</td>\n<td>Max Spell Level</td>\n<td>Ref</td>\n<td>Fort</td>\n<td>Will</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d6]]/II</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d20]]</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>+0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d8]]/II</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d20]]</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>+0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d8]]/II</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d20]]</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d10]]/II</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d20]]</td>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d10]]/II</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d20+1]]d14</td>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d12]]/II</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d20+1]]d16</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d12]]/II</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d20+1]]d20</td>\n<td>19</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d14]]/II</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d20+1]]d20</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9</td>\n<td>+5</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d14]]/II</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d20+1]]d20</td>\n<td>12</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>+5</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d16]]/II</td>\n<td>[[/roll 1d20+1]]d20+[[/roll 1d14]]</td>\n<td>14</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>+6</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.IdgRWqSLloDR89FW]{Table 1-17: Elf Titles}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 99.2816%; text-align: center;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Table 1-17: Elf Titles</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 20.9579%;\">Level</td>\n<td style=\"width: 78.3237%;\">Title (all alignments)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 20.9579%;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 78.3237%;\">Wanderer</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 20.9579%;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 78.3237%;\">Seer</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 20.9579%;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 78.3237%;\">Quester</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 20.9579%;\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 78.3237%;\">Savant</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 20.9579%;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 78.3237%;\">Elder</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
{"_id":"w3uO0MwTjitdUucu","name":"Table 9-8: Unique Powers","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.91XXvWM8n2kgESzO"}},"content":"<p>pg. 384</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-tables.jfmyPZTn2BLHy208]{Table 9-8: Unique Powers}</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1453%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\">[[/roll 1d12]]<strong><br /></strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\"><strong>Power</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">Heal any wounds or a specific kind of injury (i.e., restore sight to the blind, let the lame walk again, bind the bloodiest of wounds, etc.)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">2</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">See the future, either completely or a particular slice (i.e., see a character&rsquo;s doom, his future love, his descendents, his last breath, etc.), through some specific method (read palms, tea leaves, entrails, etc.), or simply via a third eye</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">3</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">Grant life to an unliving thing (i.e., allow the creation of Pinocchio-type creatures, animate a golem, etc.)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">4</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">Restore life to a dead creature (either permanently or temporarily, and not always with completely desirable results; i.e., the wounds of the dead creature may not be healed in the process)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">5</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">Speak with the dead, sometimes with conditions: only bodies occupied by the character&rsquo;s same soul, only ghosts that still walk the earth, only ancestors of the character, only if the body is present, only those dead that are now un-dead, only souls that have never been resurrected, etc.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">6</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">Travel to distant realms, sometimes with specific conditions: only the realms of the dead, only the lands of the angels, only the elemental planes, etc.; but generally with flawless accuracy and at-will</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">7</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">Tame animals, monsters, un-dead, etc.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">8</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">Cancel curses, restore good fortune, or end bad luck</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">9</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">Control the weather, in ways either small or large</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">10</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">Know the past of a person or item or animal by touching it or simply by description (i.e., reciting the complete history of a person&rsquo;s life story, or the provenance of an item including all owners since it was created, etc.)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">11</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">Locate missing people</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 7.75797%;\" align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: BookAntiqua;\">12</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 91.5236%;\" align=\"left\">Summon monsters from beyond</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
{"_id":"wZf6zVPSjIHDsb4a","name":"Table 9-14: Demon Special Attacks (roll 1d4-1 times)","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.CF5eBAaRQ3zFYfWK"}},"content":"<p>pg. 404</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-tables.Iw8UWh7iJtXi25gh]{Table 9-14: Demon Special Attacks (Roll [[/roll 1d4-1]] times)}</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"70\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"274\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"29\">[[/roll d12]]</td>\n<td align=\"left\"><strong>Special Attack</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"27\">1</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Poison*</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"27\">2</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Curse**</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"24\">3</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Drain ability score</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"23\">4</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Drain XP</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"27\">5</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Sleep</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">6</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Paralysis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">7</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Possession</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">8</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Drain blood</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">9</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Spells***</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">10</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Suffocation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">11</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Swallow whole</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\">12</td>\n<td align=\"left\">Breath weapon</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">* See Appendix P.<br />** See Appendix C.<br />*** Of wizard type. [[/roll 1d4]] spells of random level; spell check modifier equal to HD.</span></em></p>"}
